It turns out that after a few decades the minds of those who have taken the drug begin slowly regressing to a childlike state. This regression doesn't happen at the same speed as a child's mental development only it reverse, it's a much slower process. However, slowly but surely, all the young people are becoming more childlike in their thinking and behavior. It turns out that after a few decades the minds of those who have taken the drug begin slowly regressing to a childlike state. This regression doesn't happen at the same speed as a child's mental development only it reverse, it's a much slower process. However, slowly but surely, all the young people are becoming more childlike in their thinking and behavior. There is a panic and the government is at a loss as to how to deal with this unprecedented crisis. The government decides to take the drug away from the young people, but this only makes the problem worse. The side effects seem to be permanent and when people stop taking the drug they only proceed at a faster pace. Soon some of the people who had taken the drug are in an infantile state unable to care for themselves. The government decides to put them in a special facility. People are required to work as caretakers for these unnatural babies but many of those who weren't allowed the drug are too old now to take on that responsibility. The government decides to hire young people to do the job. It's a strange situat

This regression doesn't happen at the same speed as a child's mental development only it reverse, it's a much slower process. The government decides to take the drug away from the young people, but this only makes the problem worse.
